Revision history for ssh

0.07 2026-04-24
 - make `ssh.add` skip `ssh-add` when the key fingerprint is already loaded in the active agent
 - return already loaded keys in `already_loaded` instead of prompting for the passphrase again

0.06 2026-04-24
 - fix `ssh.add`, collector checks, and list mode to use the active ssh-agent socket selected by `ensure_agent`
 - handle agent start cases where the live socket differs from the default managed socket path
 - return the active socket in add, collector, and list output

0.05 2026-04-23
 - add `dashboard ssh.list` to show all managed keys from the skill registry
 - add `dashboard ssh.ls` as an alias of `dashboard ssh.list`
 - support `-o table` by default and `-o json` for structured output
 - include each key's registry entry, expanded file path, loaded status, and fingerprint when available

0.04 2026-04-23
 - fix installed `ssh.add` behavior for stale `SSH_AUTH_SOCK` values by using quiet health checks
 - reject explicit missing keys before writing them to the registry or running `ssh-add`
 - remove stale remembered entries when an explicitly requested key is missing
 - remove Perl file/line suffixes from expected user-facing command errors
 - add a shell startup bridge that sources `~/.ssh/ssh-agent/agent.env` from the user's shell profile
 - include `shell_env` and `shell_source` in successful add output so the current shell can be updated explicitly

0.03 2026-04-23
 - move managed ssh-agent socket and env files from `~/.developer-dashboard/ssh-agent` to `~/.ssh/ssh-agent`
 - keep DD runtime roots clean for users who track their DD folder with git

0.02 2026-04-23
 - make the SSH config bridge point at the active shared agent socket instead of always pointing at the default managed socket
 - read the saved agent env file when a new session has no `SSH_AUTH_SOCK`
 - add tests for saved agent env parsing and active socket bridging

0.01 2026-04-23
 - bootstrap the ssh skill with smart key registration, managed ssh-agent socket repair, and collector-ready key checks
